                <img src="figures/KA_squeeze_theorem_answer2.png" data-gallery="squeeze" class="gallery-thumb h-16 md:h-20 cursor-pointer border-4 border-transparent hover:border-indigo-500 rounded-md">
                <img src="figures/KA_squeeze_theorem_answer3.png" data-gallery="squeeze" class="gallery-thumb h-16 md:h-20 cursor-pointer border-4 border-transparent hover:border-indigo-500 rounded-md">
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Slide 4: Discontinuities Intuition -->
        <div class="slide w-full max-w-4xl h-full flex-col items-center justify-center text-center bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-8">
            <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Types of Discontinuities</h2>
            <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mb-6">
                <strong>The Idea:</strong> A discontinuity is any place where a function has a break in its graph. We classify these breaks based on how the function behaves around them. The main types are removable (a hole), jump (a sudden leap), and infinite (a vertical asymptote).
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-2xl italic">
                <strong>Metaphor:</strong> Think of the function as a road. A **removable** discontinuity is a small pothole you can easily patch. A **jump** is like a drawbridge that's open, forcing you to teleport to the other side. An **infinite** discontinuity is a cliff where the road goes off to the sky or down into a canyon.
            </p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Slide 5: Discontinuities Gallery -->
        <div class="slide w-full max-w-4xl h-full flex-col items-center justify-center bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-8">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Examples: Types of Discontinuities</h3>
            <!-- Main Image Display -->
            <img id="discontinuity-main" src="figures/KA_discontinuity_1.png" alt="Discontinuity Example" class="max-w-full h-auto rounded-lg shadow-md mb-4" style="max-height: 400px;">
            <!-- Thumbnails -->
            <div class="flex gap-2 md:gap-4">
